{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"name":"ir","display_name":"R","language":"R"},"language_info":{"name":"R","codemirror_mode":"r","pygments_lexer":"r","mimetype":"text/x-r-source","file_extension":".r","version":"4.0.5"}},"nbformat_minor":4,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# **Video Game Sales** ðŸ‘¾\n\n<img src=\"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1627160280085-2dbb99a7c4ff?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&ixid=MnwxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1752&q=80\" alt=\"Rafael Hoyos Weht\" width=\"800\"/>","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Table of Content","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"* [Introduction](#introduction)\n* [Sales share on the markets](#Section-one)\n* [Game sales worldwide between 1980 and 2016](#Section-two)\n* [Analysis of Genre category](#Section-three)\n    - [Genre Frequency Distribution](#Section-three-one)\n    - [Number of sales by genre on each market](#Section-three-two)\n* [Analysis of platform category](#Section-four)\n    - [Platform Frequency Distribution](#Section-four-one)\n    - [Platform Producers Frequency Distribution](#Section-four-two)\n* [Number of Sales per Platform](#Section-five)\n* [The Best Selling Games in the World](#Section-six)","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<a id=\"section-one\"></a>\n# Introduction\n## Objective","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Since the 1980s, video games have become an increasingly important part of the entertainment industry, and whether they are also a form of art is a matter of dispute. I really enjoy playing games and decided it will be fascinating to analyse couple of trends like te most popular platform or genre, the most profitable market, etc. Accordingly, in this project I will deal only with exploratory analysis with a objective to understand how the data is distributed and generate insight for future data-driven decision-making. Moreover, this analysis aims to explore as much as possible the data in a simple and informative way. Below is a sketch of all the stages made in these notebooks, following a logical and intuitive sequence to facilitate the understanding of the data. ","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"The R libraries are installed and aliased for easy reading.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"install.packages('ggplot2')\ninstall.packages('hrbrthemes')\ninstall.packages('viridis')\ninstall.packages('plotly')\ninstall.packages('ggthemes')\ninstall.packages('dplyr')","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-02T02:58:43.317669Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-02T02:58:43.320337Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-02T03:04:44.03776Z"},"_kg_hide-output":true,"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Visualizations\nlibrary(ggplot2)\nlibrary(hrbrthemes)\nlibrary(viridis)\nlibrary(plotly)\nlibrary(ggthemes)\n\n# Data Manipulation\nlibrary(dplyr)","metadata":{"_kg_hide-output":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-02T03:04:44.042135Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-02T03:04:44.086045Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-02T03:04:45.107769Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"The following file is selected and copied for analysis. From first observations I have mentioned that data from 2017:2020 is incomplete, removing data with the NaN values will definitely help with the analysis!","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Loading the database \ndata <- read.csv(\"../input/videogamesales/vgsales.csv\", stringsAsFactors = FALSE)\n\n# Removing the Rank column\ndata$Rank <- NULL\n\n# Filtering only the records of interest for this study, removing the records with Year = NaN and records with the year above 2016\ndata <- data[data$Year != \"N/A\" & data$Year != \"2017\" & data$Year != \"2020\", ]\ndata$Year <- factor(data$Year)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-02T03:04:45.110805Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-02T03:04:45.112488Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-02T03:04:45.247284Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"What are some quick summary statistics we'd want to know about each data frame? Letâ€™s have a look at summary statistics of the data sets:","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"str(data)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-02T03:04:45.250358Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-02T03:04:45.25282Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-02T03:04:45.296423Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"data %>%  \n  select(Platform,\n         Year,\n         Genre,\n         NA_Sales,\n         EU_Sales,\n         JP_Sales,\n         Other_Sales,\n         Global_Sales\n        ) %>%\n  summary()","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-02T03:04:45.298765Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-02T03:04:45.300158Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-02T03:04:45.376544Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"For these sales, though the minimums, several quantiles, and medians are small, the maximums are high, which means there are real good sale games among them. There is a clear dominance of sales on the North American market. Let's construct a data frame to visualise observations.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<a id=\"section-one\"></a>\n# 1. Sales share on the markets","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"market_means <- data.frame(Mean = c(mean(data$NA_Sales), mean(data$EU_Sales), mean(data$JP_Sales), mean(data$Other_Sales), mean(data$Global_Sales)))\nrow.names(market_means) <- c(\"North America \", \"Europe\", \"Japan\", \"Rest of the world \", \"Worldwide\")\nmarket_means$Mean_round <- round(market_means$Mean ,digit=2)\nmarket_means","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-02T03:04:45.379052Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-02T03:04:45.380567Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-02T03:04:45.41089Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Plot\ntheme_set(theme_bw())\n\nggplot(data = market_means, mapping = aes(x=row.names(market_means), y=Mean_round)) + \n  geom_point(size=5) + \n  geom_segment(aes(x=row.names(market_means), \n                   xend=row.names(market_means), \n                   y=0, \n                   yend=Mean_round)) +\n  geom_label(mapping = aes(label=Mean_round), fill = \"darkblue\", size = 3.5, color = \"white\", fontface = \"bold\", hjust=.5) +\n  ggtitle(\"Sales share on the markets\") +\n  xlab(\"Markets\") +\n  ylab(\"Mean of Sales\") +\n  labs(caption=\"source: vgsales.csv\") +\n  theme(\n    plot.title = element_text(size = 24, hjust = .5, face = \"bold\"),\n    axis.title.x = element_text(size = 18, hjust = .5, face = \"italic\"),\n    axis.title.y = element_text(size = 18, hjust = .5, face = \"italic\"),\n    axis.text.x = element_text(size = 10, face = \"bold\", angle = 0),\n    axis.text.y = element_text(size = 10, face = \"bold\"),\n    legend.position = \"none\")","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-02T03:04:45.413337Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-02T03:04:45.414779Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-02T03:04:45.983165Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<a id=\"section-two\"></a>\n# 2. Game sales worldwide between 1980 and 2016","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"What is the golden period of game sales? Let's take a look at pattern of Game Sales worldwide between 1980 and 2016.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"global_sales_by_year <- aggregate(list(Global_Sales = data$Global_Sales), list(Year = data$Year), sum)\nglobal_sales_by_year <- global_sales_by_year[order(global_sales_by_year$Global_Sales),]\na <- c()\nfor(i in 1:nrow(global_sales_by_year)){\n    a <- c(a, i)\n}\nrow.names(global_sales_by_year) <- a\nglobal_sales_by_year","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-02T03:04:45.985769Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-02T03:04:45.987303Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-02T03:04:46.050523Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"options(repr.plot.width = 15, repr.plot.height = 5)\nggplot(data = global_sales_by_year, mapping = aes(x = Year, y = Global_Sales)) +\n         geom_segment(aes(xend=Year, yend=0, color = Year), size = 1.5, alpha = .8) +\n         geom_point(mapping = aes(fill = Year), size = 3, shape = 21) +\n         geom_line(group = 1, size = 0.7, linetype = 10, color = \"blue\") +\n         ggtitle(\"Game sales worldwide between 1980 and 2016\") +\n         xlab(\"\") +\n         ylab(\"Global Sales\") +\n         labs(caption=\"source: vgsales.csv\") +\n         theme(plot.margin = margin(1, 0.2, 1, 0.2, \"cm\"),\n               plot.title = element_text(size = 25, face = \"bold\", hjust = .5),\n               axis.title.x = element_text(size = 12, hjust = .5, face = \"italic\"),\n               axis.title.y = element_text(size = 12, hjust = .5, face = \"italic\"),\n               axis.text.x = element_text(size = 10, angle = 0),\n               axis.text.y = element_text(size = 12, face = \"bold\"),\n               legend.position = \"none\")","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-02T03:13:23.169907Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-02T03:13:23.172098Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-02T03:13:23.485563Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"The figure shows that there were very few sales before 1996. However, starrting from 1996 the sales increased slowly.The golden period for games are from 2007 to 2010. Unfortunately, there is no data about 2019 to 2020 period which had to be significantly affected by covid, which hypothetically could positively affect Global Sales.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<a id=\"section-three\"></a>\n# 3. Analysis of Genre category","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"print(\"Count of unique values\")\ntable(data$Genre)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-02T03:04:46.412765Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-02T03:04:46.414256Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-02T03:04:46.433843Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"From the above we can see that \"Action\" and \"Sports\" are most common genres among games, let's construct a frequency distribution to visualise the outcome.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<a id=\"subsection-three-one\"></a>\n### 3.1 Genre Frequency Distribution","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Construct a frequency distribution, sum of the numbers in each category (Genre) based on how many times it shows up. \n\nfreq_genre <- data.frame(cbind(Frequency = table(data$Genre), Percent = prop.table(table(data$Genre)) * 100))\nfreq_genre <- freq_genre[order(freq_genre$Frequency, decreasing = T), ]\nfreq_genre\n\n","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-02T03:04:46.436161Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-02T03:04:46.437593Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-02T03:04:46.47197Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Plot\n\nggplot(data = freq_genre, mapping = aes(x = Frequency, y = row.names(freq_genre))) +\n  geom_bar(stat = \"identity\", mapping = aes(fill = row.names(freq_genre), color = row.names(freq_genre)), alpha = .7, size = 1.1) +\n  geom_label(mapping = aes(label=Frequency), fill = \"darkblue\", size = 3.5, color = \"white\", fontface = \"bold\", hjust=.5) +\n  ggtitle(\"Genre Frequency Distribution\") +\n  xlab(\"Genres\") +\n  ylab(\"Frequency\") +\n  coord_flip() +\n  labs(caption=\"source: vgsales.csv\") +\n  theme(\n    plot.title = element_text(size = 24, hjust = .5, face = \"bold\"),\n    axis.title.x = element_text(size = 18, hjust = .5, face = \"italic\"),\n    axis.title.y = element_text(size = 18, hjust = .5, face = \"italic\"),\n    axis.text.x = element_text(size = 10, face = \"bold\", angle = 0),\n    axis.text.y = element_text(size = 10, face = \"bold\"),\n    legend.position = \"none\")","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-02T03:04:46.474361Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-02T03:04:46.475817Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-02T03:04:46.822422Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<a id=\"subsection-three-two\"></a>\n### 3.2 Number of sales by genre on each market","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"All the video games in the dataset fall into twelve genres. Most of the games belong to the â€˜Actionâ€™ and â€˜Sportâ€™ genre. But that does not mean that these genres have made the most sales. Letâ€™s plot some graphs to get a clear picture.\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# NA_Sales\ngenre_sales_NA <- aggregate(list(NA_Sales = data$NA_Sales), list(Genre = data$Genre), sum)\ngenre_sales_NA <- genre_sales_NA[order(genre_sales_NA$NA_Sales, decreasing = T), ]\n\n# EU_Sales\ngenre_sales_EU <- aggregate(list(EU_Sales = data$EU_Sales), list(Genre = data$Genre), sum)\ngenre_sales_EU <- genre_sales_EU[order(genre_sales_EU$EU_Sales, decreasing = T), ]\n\n\n# JP_Sales\ngenre_sales_JP <- aggregate(list(JP_Sales = data$JP_Sales), list(Genre = data$Genre), sum)\ngenre_sales_JP <- genre_sales_JP[order(genre_sales_JP$JP_Sales, decreasing = T), ]\n\n# Other_Sales\ngenre_sales_Other <- aggregate(list(Other_Sales = data$Other_Sales), list(Genre = data$Genre), sum)\ngenre_sales_Other <- genre_sales_Other[order(genre_sales_Other$Other_Sales, decreasing = T), ]\n\n# Global_Sales\ngenre_sales_Global <- aggregate(list(Global_Sales = data$Global_Sales), list(Genre = data$Genre), sum)\ngenre_sales_Global <- genre_sales_Global[order(genre_sales_Global$Global_Sales, decreasing = T), ]\n","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-02T03:04:46.824937Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-02T03:04:46.826421Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-02T03:04:46.901637Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Plots\n# Number of sales per genre in North America\noptions(repr.plot.width = 15, repr.plot.height = 5)\nggplot(data = genre_sales_NA, mapping = aes(x = Genre, y = NA_Sales)) +\n  geom_segment(aes(xend=Genre, yend=0, color = Genre), size = 1.3, alpha = 1.5) +\n  geom_point(mapping = aes(fill = Genre), size = 5, shape = 21, alpha = .7) +\n  geom_line(group = 1, size = 0.7, linetype = 10, color = \"red\", alpha = .7) +\n  xlab(\"Genres\") +\n  ylab(\"Sales\") +\n  ggtitle(\"Number of sales by genre in North America (in mm)\") +\n  labs(caption=\"source: vgsales.csv\") +\n  theme(\n    plot.title = element_text(size = 24, hjust = .5, face = \"bold\"),\n    axis.title.x = element_text(size = 18, hjust = .5, face = \"italic\"),\n    axis.title.y = element_text(size = 18, hjust = .5, face = \"italic\"),\n    axis.text.x = element_text(size = 10, face = \"bold\", angle = 0),\n    axis.text.y = element_text(size = 10, face = \"bold\"),\n    legend.position = \"none\")\n\n# Number of sales per genre in Europe\n\nggplot(data = genre_sales_EU, mapping = aes(x = Genre, y = EU_Sales)) +\n  geom_segment(aes(xend=Genre, yend=0, color = Genre), size = 1.3, alpha = 1.5) +\n  geom_point(mapping = aes(fill = Genre), size = 5, shape = 21, alpha = .7) +\n  geom_line(group = 1, size = 0.7, linetype = 10, color = \"red\", alpha = .7) +\n  xlab(\"Genres\") +\n  ylab(\"Sales\") +\n  ggtitle(\"Number of sales by genre in Europe (in mm)\") +\n  labs(caption=\"source: vgsales.csv\") +\n  theme(\n    plot.title = element_text(size = 24, hjust = .5, face = \"bold\"),\n    axis.title.x = element_text(size = 18, hjust = .5, face = \"italic\"),\n    axis.title.y = element_text(size = 18, hjust = .5, face = \"italic\"),\n    axis.text.x = element_text(size = 10, face = \"bold\", angle = 0),\n    axis.text.y = element_text(size = 10, face = \"bold\"),\n    legend.position = \"none\")\n\n# Number of sales per genre in Japan\n\nggplot(data = genre_sales_JP, mapping = aes(x = Genre, y = JP_Sales)) +\n  geom_segment(aes(xend=Genre, yend=0, color = Genre), size = 1.3, alpha = 1.5) +\n  geom_point(mapping = aes(fill = Genre), size = 5, shape = 21, alpha = .7) +\n  geom_line(group = 1, size = 0.7, linetype = 10, color = \"red\", alpha = .7) +\n  xlab(\"Genres\") +\n  ylab(\"Sales\") +\n  ggtitle(\"Number of sales by genre in Japan (in mm)\") +\n  labs(caption=\"source: vgsales.csv\") +\n  theme(\n    plot.title = element_text(size = 24, hjust = .5, face = \"bold\"),\n    axis.title.x = element_text(size = 18, hjust = .5, face = \"italic\"),\n    axis.title.y = element_text(size = 18, hjust = .5, face = \"italic\"),\n    axis.text.x = element_text(size = 10, face = \"bold\", angle = 0),\n    axis.text.y = element_text(size = 10, face = \"bold\"),\n    legend.position = \"none\")\n\n# Number of sales per genre in rest of the world\n\nggplot(data = genre_sales_Other, mapping = aes(x = Genre, y = Other_Sales)) +\n  geom_segment(aes(xend=Genre, yend=0, color = Genre), size = 1.3, alpha = 1.5) +\n  geom_point(mapping = aes(fill = Genre), size = 5, shape = 21, alpha = .7) +\n  geom_line(group = 1, size = 0.7, linetype = 10, color = \"red\", alpha = .7) +\n  xlab(\"Genres\") +\n  ylab(\"Sales\") +\n  ggtitle(\"Number of sales by genre in ROW (in mm)\") +\n  labs(caption=\"source: vgsales.csv\") +\n  theme(\n    plot.title = element_text(size = 24, hjust = .5, face = \"bold\"),\n    axis.title.x = element_text(size = 18, hjust = .5, face = \"italic\"),\n    axis.title.y = element_text(size = 18, hjust = .5, face = \"italic\"),\n    axis.text.x = element_text(size = 10, face = \"bold\", angle = 0),\n    axis.text.y = element_text(size = 10, face = \"bold\"),\n    legend.position = \"none\")","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-02T03:04:46.904445Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-02T03:04:46.906033Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-02T03:04:48.060767Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<a id=\"section-four\"></a>\n# 4. Analysis of platform category","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"print(\"Count of unique values\")\ntable(data$Platform)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-02T03:04:48.063288Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-02T03:04:48.064813Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-02T03:04:48.085431Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"From the above we can see that \"PS2\" and \"DS\" are most common platforms among games, let's construct a frequency distribution to visualise the outcome.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<a id=\"section-four-one\"></a>\n### 4.1 Platform Frequency Distribution","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Construct a frequency distribution, sum of the numbers in each category (Platform) based on how many times it shows up. \n\nfreq_platform <- data.frame(cbind(Frequency = table(data$Platform), Percent = prop.table(table(data$Platform)) * 100))\nfreq_platform <- freq_platform[order(freq_platform$Frequency, decreasing = T), ]\nfreq_platform\n\n","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-02T03:04:48.088047Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-02T03:04:48.096141Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-02T03:04:48.139845Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Plot\n\nggplot(data = freq_platform, mapping = aes(x = Frequency, y = row.names(freq_platform))) +\n  geom_bar(stat = \"identity\", mapping = aes(fill = row.names(freq_platform), color = row.names(freq_platform)), alpha = 0.7, size = 0.5) +\n  geom_label(mapping = aes(label=Frequency), fill = \"darkblue\", size = 2.4, color = \"white\", fontface = \"bold\", hjust=.5) +\n  ggtitle(\"Platform Frequency Distribution\") +\n  xlab(\"Frequency\") +\n  ylab(\"Platform\") +\n  coord_flip() +\n  labs(caption=\"source: vgsales.csv\") +\n  theme(\n    plot.title = element_text(size = 24, hjust = .5, face = \"bold\"),\n    axis.title.x = element_text(size = 18, hjust = .5, face = \"italic\"),\n    axis.title.y = element_text(size = 18, hjust = .5, face = \"italic\"),\n    axis.text.x = element_text(size = 10, face = \"bold\", angle = 0),\n    axis.text.y = element_text(size = 10, face = \"bold\"),\n    legend.position = \"none\")\n","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-02T03:04:48.142527Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-02T03:04:48.14409Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-02T03:04:48.655499Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<a id=\"section-four-two\"></a>\n### 4.2 Platform Producers Frequency Distribution","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"There is a clear competition between different platforms, let's see the bigest producer.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Regroup platform as Platform_type\nfreq_platform$Platform = c('DS', 'PS2', 'PS3', 'Wii', 'X360', 'PSP', 'PS', 'PC', 'GBA', 'XB', 'GC', '3DS', 'PSV', 'PS4', 'N64', 'SNES', 'XOne', 'SAT', 'WiiU', '2600', 'NES', 'GB', 'DC', 'GEN', 'NG', 'SCD', 'WS', '3DO', 'TG16', 'GG', 'PCFX')\npc <- c(\"PC\")\nxbox <- c(\"X360\", \"XB\", \"XOne\")\nnintendo <- c(\"Wii\", \"WiiU\", \"N64\", \"GC\", \"NES\", \"3DS\", \"DS\") \nplaystation <- c(\"PS\", \"PS2\", \"PS3\", \"PS4\", \"PSP\", \"PSV\")\nplatforms <- freq_platform %>%\n  mutate(Platform_type = ifelse(Platform %in% pc, \"PC\",\n                           ifelse(Platform %in% xbox, \"Xbox\",\n                             ifelse(Platform %in% nintendo, \"Nintendo\", \n                               ifelse(Platform %in% playstation, \"Playstation\", \"Others\"))))) ","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-05-02T03:10:10.160617Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-05-02T03:10:10.162271Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-05-02T03:10:10.194055Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_